Description: Fragment of amygdaloid handle from a Knidian pottery transport amphora. Clay medium red-brown; mixed inclusions. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription.
Type series: KT (1065 in Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Names, Epikrates and Nikasiboulos. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.59, 18. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0274)
